convexity of sets, combinations, functions

Basically:

  • convex sets- any full shape without squishes?
  • convex functions - any bowl / u shaped function without dips or valleys
  • convex combinations - a slider between the points in a set that ensures the resulting value always stays within the sets
  • convex hull - minimal convex set such that it contains all points of S and there is no smaller convex set which is more minimal
